setSrcType

public void setSrcType(short srcType)

setSource

public void setSource(byte[] src)
Sets the source byte array with data of a .ddd file. The byte array will be parsed and a XMLDumper object will be created internally. Depending on the data the XMLDumper object will be a CardData or a VehicleUnitData object. The created object can then be copied with the getXMLDumper() method.

Specified by:
setSource in interface DataSource
Parameters:
src - byte array with data of a .ddd file

processSource

public boolean processSource()
Processes the source set by setSource(byte[]) as the type of data set by setSrcType(short).

Returns:
true, if processing was successful

setSourceFile

public void setSourceFile(java.lang.String srcfile)
Sets the source .ddd file. The file will be parsed and a XMLDumper object will be created internally. Depending on the data the XMLDumper object will be a CardData or a VehicleUnitData object. The created object can then be copied with the getXMLDumper() method.

Parameters:
srcfile - the location of the .ddd file that will be processed

processSourceFile

public boolean processSourceFile()
processes the source file set by setSourceFile()
